But nothing is going to dampen the spirit of this holiday crowd, I can tell you that.

256
00:21:23,987 --> 00:21:26,478
Oh, here they are. Here come the nuts.

257
00:22:43,570 --> 00:22:47,337
Would it be indecent to ask the grandparents to stay at a hotel?

258
00:22:48,576 --> 00:22:51,375
Can we at least forbid them to answer the phone?

259
00:22:51,445 --> 00:22:54,209
Alexander called this morning and Grandpa Clark told him...

260
00:22:54,281 --> 00:22:57,513
...I couldn't come to the phone 'cause I was going to the bathroom.

261
00:22:57,586 --> 00:22:59,747
We're all making sacrifices, Audrey.

262
00:23:00,088 --> 00:23:00,986
Everybody?

263
00:23:01,056 --> 00:23:05,084
Do you sleep with your brother? Do you know how sick and twisted that is?

264
00:23:05,160 --> 00:23:09,324
I'm sleeping with your father. Don't be so dramatic.

265
00:23:09,898 --> 00:23:14,269
I have nightmares about what he does in bed alone when I'm not lying next to him.

266
00:23:14,504 --> 00:23:17,838
I don't know what to say except it's Christmas...

267
00:23:18,274 --> 00:23:20,105
...and we're all in misery.

268
00:23:21,010 --> 00:23:23,570
Ellen, are you smoking again?

269
00:23:24,480 --> 00:23:25,913
No!

270
00:23:37,162 --> 00:23:39,629
Dad, where do you want these reindeer?

271
00:23:39,930 --> 00:23:42,125
Just put them on the lawn, Russ.

272
00:23:44,369 --> 00:23:46,269
I can't find the Santa Claus.

273
00:23:47,539 --> 00:23:50,440
It's in the basement. We'll get it later.

274
00:24:46,435 --> 00:24:48,767
Clark? Dinner's ready.

275
00:24:49,770 --> 00:24:52,001
Okay, honey. I'm starving.

276
00:25:11,126 --> 00:25:15,496
Obviously something broke the window. Something hit the stereo.

277
00:25:25,242 --> 00:25:27,904
And why is the carpet all wet, Todd?

278
00:25:28,044 --> 00:25:30,411
I don't know, Margo.

279
00:25:38,323 --> 00:25:41,486
You wanna hurry this up, Clark? I'm freezing my baguettes off.

280
00:25:41,559 --> 00:25:45,858
Two hundred and fifty strands of lights, 100 individual bulbs per strand...

281
00:25:46,264 --> 00:25:49,860
...for a grand total of 25,000 imported Italian twinkle lights.

282
00:25:52,270 --> 00:25:53,431
Twenty-five thousand.

283
00:25:53,571 --> 00:25:55,767
I hope nobody I know drives by...

284
00:25:55,941 --> 00:25:59,569
...and sees me standing in the yard, staring at my house in my pajamas.

285
00:25:59,645 --> 00:26:02,773
If they know your dad, they won't think anything of it.

286
00:26:02,849 --> 00:26:04,338
Fire it up!

287
00:26:05,585 --> 00:26:09,782
I dedicate this house to the Griswold family Christmas.

288
00:26:12,992 --> 00:26:14,358
Drum roll, please.

289
00:26:16,997 --> 00:26:18,022
Drum roll.

290
00:26:32,813 --> 00:26:36,477
"Joy to the world."

291
00:26:50,833 --> 00:26:52,267
Beautiful, Clark.

292
00:26:53,236 --> 00:26:55,396
Talk about pissing your money away.

293
00:26:56,239 --> 00:27:00,641
I hope you kids see what a silly waste of resources this was.

294
00:27:00,909 --> 00:27:02,900
He worked really hard, Grandma.

295
00:27:03,146 --> 00:27:04,909
So do washing machines.

296
00:27:09,853 --> 00:27:11,753
Let's get in where it's warm.

297
00:27:12,422 --> 00:27:17,086
Clark, baby, I can picture it in my mind and it's breathtaking.

298
00:27:20,564 --> 00:27:21,724
Thanks, Mom.

299
00:27:22,433 --> 00:27:27,461
It's probably a bad bulb. You know, if one goes out, the whole thing won't work.

300
00:27:27,705 --> 00:27:30,869
If I were you, I'd personally check each one.

301
00:27:31,108 --> 00:27:32,440
I did that, Dad.

302
00:27:32,676 --> 00:27:36,545
If you need any help, give me a holler. I'll be upstairs asleep.

303
00:27:38,617 --> 00:27:42,952
I'm sorry, Daddy. It looks good, even if they're not lit.

304
00:27:44,557 --> 00:27:46,148
Thank you, sweetheart.

305
00:27:52,632 --> 00:27:55,294
Well, Dad, it was a good try.

306
00:27:55,635 --> 00:27:56,967
Thanks, Russ.

307
00:27:59,639 --> 00:28:02,005
We checked every bulb, didn't we?

308
00:28:03,709 --> 00:28:05,905
I'm sure of it.

309
00:28:09,016 --> 00:28:11,007
Maybe we ought to go up there and just...

310
00:28:11,084 --> 00:28:12,813
Geez! Look at the time.

311
00:28:13,720 --> 00:28:15,210
I have to go to bed.

312
00:28:15,722 --> 00:28:17,622
Brush my teeth, feed the hog.

313
00:28:17,724 --> 00:28:21,957
I still got some homework to do, do the laundry, wash the car...

314
00:28:27,936 --> 00:28:29,995
Don't stay up too late.

315
00:28:51,527 --> 00:28:53,894
Get off me, you little fungus.

316
00:30:55,091 --> 00:30:57,584
Where the hell is that cold coming from?

317
00:31:20,618 --> 00:31:23,611
- I need just a few more... - Pay by check, if you can.

318
00:31:24,121 --> 00:31:27,114
- Not a card? - No, it's a hassle if you have to return.

319
00:31:34,134 --> 00:31:34,963
Help!

320
00:31:35,035 --> 00:31:37,298
Daddy. Is Clark coming?

321
00:31:37,369 --> 00:31:38,631
How the hell would I know?

322
00:31:38,704 --> 00:31:39,671
Is he in the house?

323
00:31:39,738 --> 00:31:42,640
If he's not farting around with the lights, he must be.

324
00:31:42,709 --> 00:31:45,577
I'm sure he wants to come shopping and have lunch with us.

325
00:31:45,646 --> 00:31:50,548
He's got another car. He can drive. I have to eat so I can take my back pill.

326
00:35:52,774 --> 00:35:55,538
I want to take off these clothes, sit with a glass of wine...

327
00:35:55,610 --> 00:35:57,544
...and kiss every inch of your body.

328
00:35:57,612 --> 00:36:00,445
- After you shower, of course. - Of course.

329
00:36:16,799 --> 00:36:19,233
- Sparky? - Yes, honey.

330
00:36:28,278 --> 00:36:31,736
Are you out here for a reason, or are you just avoiding the family?

331
00:36:32,083 --> 00:36:34,915
I still have a couple hundred more bulbs to check.

332
00:36:35,852 --> 00:36:37,753
Meantime, I can light the Santa...

333
00:36:37,823 --> 00:36:41,087
...and the eight tiny reindeer and the "Merry Christmas" sign.

334
00:36:41,158 --> 00:36:43,649
That should look good. Ready?

335
00:36:43,928 --> 00:36:45,589
Want me to do the drum roll thing?

336
00:36:45,663 --> 00:36:47,757
No, it's okay. Here goes nothing.

337
00:36:55,507 --> 00:36:57,134
I don't understand it.

338
00:36:58,845 --> 00:37:02,076
The house lights don't work, the floodlights don't work.

339
00:37:04,349 --> 00:37:05,838
Is it plugged in?

340
00:37:06,184 --> 00:37:09,018
Do you think I would check thousands of tiny lights...

341
00:37:09,088 --> 00:37:12,148
...if I wasn't sure the extension cord was plugged in?

342
00:37:14,027 --> 00:37:16,518
You used more than one cord, didn't you?

343
00:37:18,864 --> 00:37:22,733
Maybe the kids have been fooling around with it. I'll check in the back.

344
00:37:43,658 --> 00:37:44,625
Clark!

345
00:37:47,228 --> 00:37:48,957
- Todd! - Sorry!

346
00:37:52,600 --> 00:37:55,000
Honey, I think I know what's wrong.

347
00:38:10,587 --> 00:38:11,747
I can't see!

348
00:38:30,441 --> 00:38:31,839
This ought to do it.

349
00:38:45,590 --> 00:38:46,580
I fixed it!

350
00:38:50,129 --> 00:38:52,963
Everybody! Come out quick! Look at the lights!

351
00:39:02,008 --> 00:39:03,976
- Get a towel. - Okay!

352
00:39:07,714 --> 00:39:09,476
Wait a minute! I don't believe this.

353
00:39:09,549 --> 00:39:11,847
What's all that yelling about?

354
00:39:13,653 --> 00:39:15,246
What's going on here?!

355
00:39:17,324 --> 00:39:19,155
Twenty-five thousand twinkle lights.

356
00:39:20,994 --> 00:39:22,484
What's he doing?

357
00:39:22,730 --> 00:39:24,357
I haven't the foggiest.

358
00:39:26,567 --> 00:39:28,160
What the hell?!

359
00:39:28,904 --> 00:39:30,962
What is wrong with this?!

360
00:39:32,673 --> 00:39:34,231
Damn it!

361
00:39:38,914 --> 00:39:40,313
You goddamn thing!

362
00:40:13,216 --> 00:40:14,775
Dad, it's beautiful!

363
00:40:30,735 --> 00:40:32,635
Oh, my carpet!

364
00:40:42,314 --> 00:40:44,247
Clark, it's so lovely.

365
00:40:47,586 --> 00:40:50,419
You deserve a home like this to spend Christmas in.

366
00:40:53,593 --> 00:40:56,083
It's a beaut, Clark. A beaut.

367
00:40:58,264 --> 00:41:01,257
You taught me everything I know about exterior illumination.

368
00:41:01,334 --> 00:41:03,098
Thank you, thank you.

369
00:41:04,338 --> 00:41:05,737
Russ. Audrey.

370
00:41:10,110 --> 00:41:12,442
Dear... Francis.

371
00:41:15,282 --> 00:41:18,117
I hope this adds to your enjoyment of the holidays.

372
00:41:18,453 --> 00:41:20,443
It's just wonderful.

373
00:41:22,790 --> 00:41:23,950
Arthur.

374
00:41:24,959 --> 00:41:25,948
Art.

375
00:41:27,629 --> 00:41:28,788
Dad.

376
00:41:29,298 --> 00:41:30,856
Thanks for being here.

377
00:41:31,133 --> 00:41:33,566
The little lights are not twinkling.

378
00:41:33,635 --> 00:41:36,297
I know, Art, and thanks for noticing.

379
00:41:40,809 --> 00:41:43,301
The house sure does look swell, Clark.

380
00:41:43,378 --> 00:41:44,708
Thanks, Eddie.

381
00:41:45,147 --> 00:41:49,312
I hope it enhances your holiday spirit. Dear Catherine.

382
00:41:49,652 --> 00:41:51,279
Eddie?

383
00:41:52,555 --> 00:41:55,047
The house is gorgeous, Clark.

384
00:41:56,158 --> 00:41:57,319
Eddie?

385
00:41:57,826 --> 00:42:00,819
I hope you didn't do this all on our account, Clark.

386
00:42:01,164 --> 00:42:04,760
Kids, come on out here and see what Uncle Clark's done to the house.

387
00:42:04,835 --> 00:42:05,894
Eddie?

388
00:42:13,344 --> 00:42:14,311
Eddie?

389
00:42:17,181 --> 00:42:20,174
If you don't remember, this here is Rocky.

390
00:42:21,419 --> 00:42:24,855
- Have you got a kiss for me? - Take a rain check on that, Art.

391
00:42:24,923 --> 00:42:27,756
He's got a lip fungus that ain't identified yet.

392
00:42:30,462 --> 00:42:32,452
You remember Ruby Sue?

393
00:42:34,867 --> 00:42:36,697
Oh, my gosh!

394
00:42:38,537 --> 00:42:40,334
Her eyes are not crossed anymore.

395
00:42:40,406 --> 00:42:41,874
That somethin', ain't it?

396
00:42:41,941 --> 00:42:44,034
She falls in a well, her eyes go cross.

397
00:42:44,111 --> 00:42:47,545
A mule kicks her, they go back to normal. I don't know.

398
00:42:51,218 --> 00:42:53,379
And this here is our pride and joy.

399
00:42:53,453 --> 00:42:54,887
Snots.

400
00:42:55,789 --> 00:42:56,948
Pretty name.

401
00:42:57,056 --> 00:43:00,117
We named him that 'cause he's got this sinus condition.

402
00:43:00,893 --> 00:43:04,227
Snots, you roll over and let Uncle Clark scratch your belly.

403
00:43:06,402 --> 00:43:09,733
You never seen a set on a dog like this one's got, Clark.

404
00:43:10,571 --> 00:43:12,198
That's okay, Eddie.

405
00:43:12,573 --> 00:43:15,235
That's somethin', ain't it? You pet him on the belly...

406
00:43:15,309 --> 00:43:17,504
...and he'll love you till the day you die.

407
00:43:17,578 --> 00:43:20,172
I really shouldn't. My hands are all chapped.

408
00:43:20,749 --> 00:43:25,412
We were going to call, but Eddie wanted to make it a surprise.

409
00:43:25,654 --> 00:43:26,985
You surprised?

410
00:43:27,256 --> 00:43:28,280
Surprised, Eddie?

411
00:43:28,590 --> 00:43:30,888
If I woke up tomorrow with my head sewn to the carpet...

412
00:43:31,059 --> 00:43:33,493
...I wouldn't be more surprised than I am right now.

413
00:43:35,764 --> 00:43:37,756
We have plenty of room.

414
00:43:39,936 --> 00:43:43,497
Plenty of towels. Plenty of everything.

415
00:43:45,107 --> 00:43:49,101
We're pretty well set up here in the RV. It's a little tight but...

416
00:43:49,678 --> 00:43:51,203
...we didn't come to impose.

417
00:43:51,280 --> 00:43:53,113
There's plenty of room.

418
00:43:53,551 --> 00:43:55,610
Quit being so damn polite, Ed.

419
00:43:56,421 --> 00:44:01,686
Catherine and I are pretty comfy in there, but maybe you folks wouldn't mind...

420
00:44:01,758 --> 00:44:03,454
...the youngsters shacking up with you.

421
00:44:03,527 --> 00:44:05,358
After that long drive...

422
00:44:05,463 --> 00:44:08,126
...we could use a little private time together.

423
00:44:08,967 --> 00:44:14,233
Honey, why don't you get the kids' things. Don't forget the rubber sheets and gerbils.

424
00:44:14,306 --> 00:44:16,136
I'll show you the home.

425
00:44:54,249 --> 00:44:56,240
That's a honey of a tree, Clark.

426
00:44:57,185 --> 00:44:58,344
Is it real?

427
00:44:59,353 --> 00:45:01,117
I dug it out of the ground myself.

428
00:45:01,188 --> 00:45:02,519
Is that a fact?

429
00:45:03,023 --> 00:45:04,719
Get out of there, Snots!

430
00:45:04,791 --> 00:45:05,780
Don't worry about it.

431
00:45:05,859 --> 00:45:08,384
A little tree water ain't gonna hurt him.

432
00:45:08,530 --> 00:45:11,465
Before we left, he drank a half a quart of Pennzoil.

433
00:45:11,533 --> 00:45:14,366
He lifted his leg the next mornin'...

434
00:45:16,739 --> 00:45:19,606
If he drinks the water out of there, the tree's gonna dry up.

435
00:45:19,675 --> 00:45:21,370
Come on out of there.

436
00:45:22,710 --> 00:45:27,205
Get out of there. Go in the kitchen and get something to eat.

437
00:45:27,951 --> 00:45:29,645
He's cute, ain't he?

438
00:45:29,718 --> 00:45:33,620
Only problem is, he's got a little bit of Mississippi leg hound in him.

439
00:45:33,889 --> 00:45:38,122
If the mood catches him right, he'll grab your leg and just go to town.

440
00:45:39,396 --> 00:45:43,231
You don't want him around if you're wearing short pants.

441
00:45:44,401 --> 00:45:45,892
A word of warning, though.

442
00:45:45,970 --> 00:45:49,200
If he does lay into you, it's best to just let him finish.

443
00:45:51,908 --> 00:45:55,503
I can't believe you're actually standing here in my living room, Eddie.

444
00:45:55,781 --> 00:45:57,248
Never thought the day would come.

445
00:45:57,316 --> 00:45:59,146
I'm excited about it, too.

446
00:46:00,251 --> 00:46:03,084
It's a cryin' shame the older kids couldn't make it.

447
00:46:06,825 --> 00:46:09,258
I'll get that. Don't worry about it. It's okay.

448
00:46:13,565 --> 00:46:17,763
I got the daughter in the clinic getting cured off the Wild Turkey.

449
00:46:18,704 --> 00:46:22,505
The older boy, bless his soul, is preparing for his career.

450
00:46:23,108 --> 00:46:24,666
- College? - Carnival.

451
00:46:25,777 --> 00:46:27,040
You gotta be proud.

452
00:46:28,615 --> 00:46:32,813
Last season, he was a pixie dust spreader on the Tilt-O-Whirl.

453
00:46:33,119 --> 00:46:36,282
He thinks that maybe next year, he'll be guessing people's weight...

454
00:46:36,355 --> 00:46:38,415
...or barking for the Yak Woman.

455
00:46:39,959 --> 00:46:41,893
- You ever see her? - No.

456
00:46:41,961 --> 00:46:45,295
She got these big horns growing right out above her ears.

457
00:46:45,532 --> 00:46:48,023
She's ugly as sin, but a sweet gal.

458
00:46:48,102 --> 00:46:49,296
And a hell of a good cook.

459
00:46:49,370 --> 00:46:52,066
Can I refill your eggnog for you? Get you something to eat?

460
00:46:52,139 --> 00:46:54,631
Drive you out to the middle of nowhere and leave you for dead?

461
00:46:54,708 --> 00:46:56,870
No, I'm doing just fine.

462
00:46:57,444 --> 00:46:58,811
Just glad to be here.

463
00:47:00,482 --> 00:47:03,144
When did you get the tenement on wheels?

464
00:47:03,985 --> 00:47:06,818
Oh, that? That's an RV.

465
00:47:08,289 --> 00:47:09,985
I borrowed it off a buddy of mine.

466
00:47:10,058 --> 00:47:12,891
He took my house, I took the RV.

467
00:47:13,829 --> 00:47:15,820
It's a good-looking vehicle, ain't it?

468
00:47:16,499 --> 00:47:18,433
It looks so nice parked in the driveway.

469
00:47:18,502 --> 00:47:21,834
It sure does. Don't you go falling in love with it.

470
00:47:22,571 --> 00:47:25,665
We're taking it with us when we leave here next month.

471
00:47:35,519 --> 00:47:38,352
Get Ed Leftic up here to look over these figures!

472
00:47:38,922 --> 00:47:41,082
Retooling. That's a great excuse.

473
00:47:43,193 --> 00:47:45,526
Retooling?! I'll retool you!

474
00:47:48,533 --> 00:47:50,524
Mr. Shirley, Merry Christmas.

475
00:47:50,934 --> 00:47:52,196
Who's that?

476
00:47:53,137 --> 00:47:54,798
It's me, Clark Griswold.

477
00:47:55,039 --> 00:47:56,439
What do you want?

478
00:47:57,542 --> 00:48:01,877
My wife and I just came up with a little something special. It's a gift.

479
00:48:02,948 --> 00:48:05,542
Put it over there with the others, Greaseball.

480
00:48:16,229 --> 00:48:20,689
By the way, I hope my report helped out at the trade show.

481
00:48:25,571 --> 00:48:27,562
I'm sure it did, Grisball.

482
00:48:28,308 --> 00:48:31,642
If you'll excuse me, I'm in the middle of an important call.

483
00:48:32,580 --> 00:48:33,945
Get me somebody.

484
00:48:34,081 --> 00:48:35,309
Anybody.

485
00:48:37,016 --> 00:48:38,677
And get me somebody while I'm waiting.

486
00:48:51,666 --> 00:48:55,830
This is a new non-caloric, silicon-based kitchen lubricant...

487
00:48:55,937 --> 00:48:57,267
...my company's been working on.

488
00:48:57,339 --> 00:49:01,035
It creates a surface 500 times more slippery than cooking oil.

489
00:49:01,108 --> 00:49:03,543
We'll fly down the hill with this stuff.

490
00:49:03,945 --> 00:49:06,005
Has anyone ever used it on a sled?

491
00:49:06,082 --> 00:49:07,549
Not that I know of.

492
00:49:10,119 --> 00:49:13,110
Don't go puttin' none of that stuff on my sled, Clark.

493
00:49:13,455 --> 00:49:16,789
- You know the metal plate in my head? - How could I forget it.

494
00:49:16,958 --> 00:49:20,794
I had it replaced. Every time Catherine raved up the microwave...

495
00:49:20,931 --> 00:49:23,763
...l'd piss in my pants and forget who I was.

496
00:49:24,134 --> 00:49:27,034
Over at the V.A., they had it replaced with a plastic one.

497
00:49:27,304 --> 00:49:29,295
That ain't as strong, so...

498
00:49:29,806 --> 00:49:31,967
I shouldn't go sailing down a hill...

499
00:49:32,041 --> 00:49:34,307
...with nothing between the ground and my brain...

500
00:49:34,379 --> 00:49:36,609
...but a piece of government plastic.

501
00:49:38,148 --> 00:49:39,911
You really think it matters, Eddie?

502
00:49:39,983 --> 00:49:42,816
The plate runs right underneath my part.

503
00:49:44,823 --> 00:49:47,155
Over here is nothing, but...

504
00:49:47,492 --> 00:49:52,327
...if this gets dented, then my hair just ain't going to look right.

505
00:49:54,999 --> 00:49:56,466
I know the feeling.

506
00:49:57,836 --> 00:50:00,305
I better try this first. See how it works.

507
00:50:00,371 --> 00:50:02,202
Be careful there, Clark.

508
00:50:02,273 --> 00:50:04,208
Nothing to worry about, Eddie.

509
00:50:04,343 --> 00:50:08,747
Going for a new, amateur-recreational- saucer-sled land-speed record...

510
00:50:09,182 --> 00:50:11,673
Clark W. Griswold, Junior!

511
00:50:12,352 --> 00:50:15,684
Remember, don't try this at home, kids. I am a professional.

512
00:50:18,858 --> 00:50:20,190
Later, dudes.

513
00:50:21,529 --> 00:50:23,520
Let her rip. Hang ten.

514
00:50:41,249 --> 00:50:42,682
It's great! I'm dead!

515
00:51:28,933 --> 00:51:30,093
Bingo.

516
00:51:43,114 --> 00:51:45,048
- You're staying late? - Hi, Bill.

517
00:51:45,116 --> 00:51:46,447
Yeah. Just...

518
00:51:47,118 --> 00:51:50,610
...finishing up a few things. Last day of the year for me.

519
00:51:51,288 --> 00:51:54,123
Have a really Merry Christmas.

520
00:51:55,460 --> 00:51:56,519
You, too.

521
00:51:59,032 --> 00:52:00,157
You okay?

522
00:52:01,233 --> 00:52:02,223
Yeah.

523
00:52:03,969 --> 00:52:06,461
Bill, did you get your bonus yet?

524
00:52:06,806 --> 00:52:08,707
Just talked to my son.

525
00:52:09,076 --> 00:52:11,909
Company messenger just brought something to my house.

526
00:52:12,379 --> 00:52:14,779
Nothing like waiting till the last minute, huh?

527
00:52:15,983 --> 00:52:17,245
You get yours?

528
00:52:19,319 --> 00:52:22,015
If it isn't at the house, I'm sure it must be on its way.

529
00:52:22,089 --> 00:52:25,924
If I don't get that bonus, I'm in it up to here.

530
00:52:26,327 --> 00:52:28,090
Don't sweat it. It'll come.

531
00:52:28,161 --> 00:52:29,424
Merry Christmas.

532
00:52:29,496 --> 00:52:30,725
Same to you.

533
00:52:50,853 --> 00:52:54,687
"'Mele Kalikimaka' is the thing to say

534
00:52:55,357 --> 00:52:57,349
"On a bright Hawaiian

535
00:52:57,593 --> 00:52:59,255
"Christmas day.

536
00:53:00,363 --> 00:53:02,524
"That's the island greeting

537
00:53:02,699 --> 00:53:05,758
"That we send to you From the land

538
00:53:06,535 --> 00:53:08,868
"Where palm trees sway.

539
00:53:09,840 --> 00:53:11,831
"Here we know that Christmas

540
00:53:12,076 --> 00:53:13,805
"Will be green and bright

541
00:53:14,278 --> 00:53:16,542
"The sun to shine by day

542
00:53:16,713 --> 00:53:18,705
"And all the stars at night.

543
00:53:19,116 --> 00:53:23,280
"'Mele Kalikimaka' is Hawaii's way

544
00:53:23,621 --> 00:53:26,785
"To say 'Merry Christmas' to you."

545
00:54:42,036 --> 00:54:43,368
Santy Claus?

546
00:54:44,474 --> 00:54:46,805
Uncle Clark, are you Santy Claus?

547
00:54:47,077 --> 00:54:47,940
What?

548
00:54:51,815 --> 00:54:53,304
What? You scared me.

549
00:54:55,384 --> 00:54:57,318
No, I'm not Santa Claus.

550
00:55:00,825 --> 00:55:02,053
I wish I was.

551
00:55:04,328 --> 00:55:06,454
What are you doing up, sweetheart?

552
00:55:08,165 --> 00:55:09,826
Rocky bit my thumb.

553
00:55:10,500 --> 00:55:13,333
Him's nervous because Christmas is almost here.

554
00:55:14,506 --> 00:55:15,972
Nervous or excited?

555
00:55:16,508 --> 00:55:17,838
Shittin' bricks.

556
00:55:19,176 --> 00:55:20,667
You shouldn't use that word.

557
00:55:20,745 --> 00:55:23,236
Sorry. Shittin' rocks.

558
00:55:26,018 --> 00:55:29,476
Him's nervous because he don't know if he's gettin' nothin'.

559
00:55:32,457 --> 00:55:35,688
I don't think he should be nervous, and you shouldn't be, either.

560
00:55:35,762 --> 00:55:38,594
'Cause if you're good, Santa knows it.

561
00:55:39,431 --> 00:55:41,796
If you believe in him and in your mom...

562
00:55:41,867 --> 00:55:43,562
...and you believe in...

563
00:55:43,869 --> 00:55:45,201
...your dad...

564
00:55:46,372 --> 00:55:50,934
...and you've been good all year round, Santa Claus will bring you something.

565
00:55:51,544 --> 00:55:54,707
Sometimes I think all that Santa crap is just bull.

566
00:55:55,215 --> 00:55:58,548
If he was so real, how come we didn't get squat last year?

567
00:55:58,785 --> 00:56:02,223
We didn't do nothin' wrong and we still got the shaft.

568
00:56:02,389 --> 00:56:06,382
Well, I happen to know for a fact that Santa Claus is real.

569
00:56:07,127 --> 00:56:09,219
And in the next couple of days...

570
00:56:09,730 --> 00:56:12,062
...somehow, I'm gonna prove it to you.

571
00:56:13,401 --> 00:56:16,461
Every year, he comes to our house. I've seen him.

572
00:56:17,739 --> 00:56:18,797
It's true?

573
00:56:19,073 --> 00:56:20,405
Cross my heart.

574
00:56:24,145 --> 00:56:26,340
It's a good idea you came to stay with us.

575
00:56:26,414 --> 00:56:30,577
I love it here. You don't gotta put on your coat to go to the bathroom.

576
00:56:30,752 --> 00:56:33,586
And your house is always parked in the same place.

577
00:56:37,093 --> 00:56:39,425
I think you better go back to bed, now.

578
00:56:43,265 --> 00:56:45,393
Okay. How come you ain't sleeping?

579
00:56:47,104 --> 00:56:49,265
I was looking for something.

580
00:56:52,944 --> 00:56:57,003
You didn't notice if a man came here and delivered a letter today, did you?

581
00:56:57,680 --> 00:56:59,512
Nope. How come?

582
00:56:59,783 --> 00:57:01,444
Just wondering.

583
00:57:07,124 --> 00:57:09,286
Now you get back to bed. Come here.

584
00:57:16,100 --> 00:57:18,898
Are you sure you ain't Santy Claus?

585
00:57:20,138 --> 00:57:21,162
I'm sure.

586
00:57:26,512 --> 00:57:28,480
I can't even afford to be an elf.

587
00:57:39,659 --> 00:57:43,822
I had two containers of K-rations... two containers...

588
00:57:44,163 --> 00:57:47,600
...and I had Spam until it was coming out of my ears!

589
00:57:58,845 --> 00:58:00,710
Aren't you having any breakfast?

590
00:58:00,780 --> 00:58:02,442
No. Not in the mood.

591
00:58:04,019 --> 00:58:05,714
What are you looking at?

592
00:58:08,190 --> 00:58:11,353
The silent majesty of a winter's morn. The clean...

593
00:58:11,525 --> 00:58:13,619
...cool chill of the holiday air.

594
00:58:13,794 --> 00:58:17,458
An asshole, in a bathrobe, emptying a chemical toilet into my sewer.

595
00:58:22,771 --> 00:58:24,295
The shitter was full.

596
00:58:25,207 --> 00:58:27,142
Have you checked our shitters, honey?

597
00:58:27,209 --> 00:58:29,701
Clark, please. He doesn't know any better.

598
00:58:30,046 --> 00:58:32,240
He ought to know it's illegal. It's a storm sewer.

599
00:58:32,314 --> 00:58:36,718
If it fills with gas, I pity the person who lights a match within ten yards of it.

600
00:58:59,243 --> 00:59:00,904
Merry Christmas.

601
00:59:01,345 --> 00:59:02,869
The shitter was full.

602
00:59:17,763 --> 00:59:22,132
I have this suspicion that Catherine and Eddie don't have presents for their kids.

603
00:59:22,201 --> 00:59:26,866
Rocky said Eddie told him Santa Claus wasn't coming this year.

604
00:59:28,942 --> 00:59:33,878
Ruby Sue said the same thing last night. How can they have nothing for their kids?

605
00:59:33,946 --> 00:59:36,039
He's been out of work for almost seven years.

606
00:59:36,116 --> 00:59:38,381
In seven years he couldn't find a job?

607
00:59:38,452 --> 00:59:42,287
Catherine says he's been holding out for a management position.

608
00:59:46,292 --> 00:59:48,056
So, how's the live bait business?

609
00:59:48,128 --> 00:59:50,961
I can't complain. How you doing?

610
00:59:51,631 --> 00:59:53,293
Not that good, actually.

611
00:59:53,568 --> 00:59:57,231
Your company kill off all them people in India not long ago?

612
00:59:57,472 --> 00:59:59,736
No, we missed out on that one.

613
01:00:00,241 --> 01:00:02,732
You're pretty set so far as shopping goes?

614
01:00:03,144 --> 01:00:05,477
Well, I can't lie to you, Clark.

615
01:00:05,814 --> 01:00:08,409
The truth is, things ain't goin' too good at all.

616
01:00:08,485 --> 01:00:11,920
You know I told you I borrowed the RV from a neighbor?

617
01:00:12,554 --> 01:00:13,543
It's mine.

618
01:00:14,122 --> 01:00:15,317
We live in it.

619
01:00:15,591 --> 01:00:19,153
I had to sell off the house, the barn, the ten acres...

620
01:00:20,163 --> 01:00:24,657
All I kept was a 50-foot plot, the pigs and the worm farm.

621
01:00:27,003 --> 01:00:30,667
If I only had back the money me and Catherine sent that TV preacher...

622
01:00:30,741 --> 01:00:33,139
...that was screwin' the hockey players.

623
01:00:34,344 --> 01:00:35,674
What about the kids?

624
01:00:36,145 --> 01:00:38,170
His kids can fend for themselves.

625
01:00:38,448 --> 01:00:39,780
Your kids.

626
01:00:41,085 --> 01:00:43,816
That's the bitch of it. I don't know what to do.

627
01:00:43,854 --> 01:00:48,348
We coasted into town on fumes. The gas money give out in Guerney.

628
01:00:52,596 --> 01:00:55,795
Ellen and I want to help you give the kids a nice Christmas.

629
01:00:55,868 --> 01:00:58,028
No, Clark, I couldn't do that.

630
01:00:58,569 --> 01:00:59,628
We insist.

631
01:00:59,870 --> 01:01:02,305
No, I'm not one for charity.

632
01:01:02,541 --> 01:01:05,977
I know that, Eddie. This isn't charity. It's family.

633
01:01:08,213 --> 01:01:10,148
I don't know about that.

634
01:01:10,382 --> 01:01:14,376
Now, come on, if you don't tell me what they want, I'll get it on my own.

635
01:01:19,559 --> 01:01:21,391
This is a surprise, Clark.

636
01:01:22,061 --> 01:01:24,222
This is a real nice surprise.

637
01:01:25,164 --> 01:01:27,725
Just a real nice surprise.

638
01:01:32,973 --> 01:01:33,996
Here's a list.

639
01:01:34,074 --> 01:01:36,564
Alphabetical, starting with Catherine.

640
01:01:37,077 --> 01:01:40,911
If it wouldn't be too much, I'd like to get something for you, Clark.

641
01:01:41,049 --> 01:01:43,540
Something really nice.

642
01:02:01,236 --> 01:02:03,032
Is your house on fire, Clark?

643
01:02:03,272 --> 01:02:05,297
No Bethany, those are Christmas lights.

644
01:02:05,374 --> 01:02:07,171
Don't throw me down, Clark.

645
01:02:07,276 --> 01:02:08,607
I'll try not to.

646
01:02:09,278 --> 01:02:11,109
Is this the airport?

647
01:02:11,380 --> 01:02:12,608
We're here!

648
01:02:12,716 --> 01:02:16,277
Me and Bethany figured out the perfect gift for you.

649
01:02:16,385 --> 01:02:19,219
Uncle Louis, you didn't have to buy me anything.

650
01:02:19,289 --> 01:02:21,621
Damn it, Bethany, he guessed it.

651
01:02:22,291 --> 01:02:23,884
That was fun.

652
01:02:24,293 --> 01:02:26,625
I love riding in cars.

653
01:02:27,632 --> 01:02:29,964
When did you move to Florida?

654
01:02:33,070 --> 01:02:35,435
Are you still dating Clark?

655
01:02:39,076 --> 01:02:41,236
You know you shouldn't have done that.

656
01:02:41,312 --> 01:02:43,804
Oh, dear. Did I break wind?

657
01:02:44,483 --> 01:02:48,509
Jesus, did the room clear out, Bethany? Hell, no.

658
01:02:48,654 --> 01:02:51,747
She means presents. You shouldn't have bought presents.

659
01:02:51,823 --> 01:02:55,759
It isn't every day somebody moves into a new house.

660
01:02:55,927 --> 01:02:58,088
They didn't move into a new house.

661
01:03:00,399 --> 01:03:01,627
In the living room.

662
01:03:03,670 --> 01:03:06,002
This house is bigger than your old one.

663
01:03:07,739 --> 01:03:09,901
Is Rusty still in the Navy?

664
01:03:11,176 --> 01:03:15,512
Why don't you go into the living room and say hello to everybody?

665
01:03:15,849 --> 01:03:18,943
Hello, everybody! I should say it?

666
01:03:23,222 --> 01:03:24,621
- Mom? - What?

667
01:03:25,025 --> 01:03:26,855
This box is meowing.

668
01:03:33,668 --> 01:03:35,294
She wrapped up her damn cat.

669
01:03:35,536 --> 01:03:38,471
- Take it in the kitchen. Open it up. - And have a cat running around?

670
01:03:38,539 --> 01:03:39,973
We can't leave it in the box.

671
01:03:40,041 --> 01:03:42,532
Why would somebody wrap up a cat in a box?

672
01:03:42,877 --> 01:03:44,845
She gets confused. She's old.

673
01:03:44,946 --> 01:03:48,040
They don't have much money, so she takes things from the house...

674
01:03:48,116 --> 01:03:50,277
...wraps them up, gives them away as presents.

675
01:03:50,351 --> 01:03:51,909
Can't wait to see what I got!

676
01:03:51,986 --> 01:03:53,647
This one here...

677
01:03:53,888 --> 01:03:55,150
...is leaking.

678
01:04:01,297 --> 01:04:02,025
Lime.

679
01:04:02,498 --> 01:04:03,965
It's her Jell-O mold.

680
01:04:04,033 --> 01:04:08,231
I'll take it, Eddie. Go into the living room and enjoy yourself.

681
01:04:11,506 --> 01:04:13,236
Let's go find your sister.

682
01:04:34,466 --> 01:04:35,626
Before we begin...

683
01:04:36,300 --> 01:04:38,928
...since this is Aunt Bethany's 80th Christmas...

684
01:04:39,437 --> 01:04:42,406
...I think she should lead us in the saying of grace.

685
01:04:46,544 --> 01:04:47,672
What, dear?

686
01:04:49,747 --> 01:04:50,578
Grace!

687
01:04:52,117 --> 01:04:55,519
Grace? She passed away 30 years ago.

688
01:04:56,556 --> 01:04:58,786
They want you to say grace.

689
01:05:01,627 --> 01:05:03,789
The blessing.

690
01:05:20,681 --> 01:05:22,081
"I pledge allegiance...

691
01:05:22,317 --> 01:05:25,979
"...to the flag of the United States of America...

692
01:05:26,419 --> 01:05:28,081
"...and to the republic...

693
01:05:28,321 --> 01:05:32,588
"...for which it stands, one nation under God, indivisible...

694
01:05:33,161 --> 01:05:36,494
"...with liberty and justice for all."

695
01:05:38,667 --> 01:05:39,395
Amen.

696
01:05:45,674 --> 01:05:49,610
Catherine, if this turkey tastes half as good as it looks...

697
01:05:49,846 --> 01:05:52,440
...I think we're all in for a very big treat.

698
01:05:56,619 --> 01:05:58,450
Save the neck for me, Clark.

699
01:06:14,972 --> 01:06:16,131
I'm sorry.

700
01:06:17,174 --> 01:06:18,232
Why are you crying?

701
01:06:18,308 --> 01:06:20,800
I told you we put it in too early.

702
01:06:21,446 --> 01:06:23,710
It's just a little dry. It's fine.

703
01:06:26,451 --> 01:06:27,508
Here's the heart.

704
01:07:28,517 --> 01:07:29,814
Aunt Bethany...

705
01:07:31,453 --> 01:07:33,579
Does your cat happen to eat Jell-O?

706
01:07:35,891 --> 01:07:37,792
I don't know about the cat...

707
01:07:38,193 --> 01:07:39,558
...but I'm enjoying it.

708
01:07:52,908 --> 01:07:53,740
Kids...

709
01:07:54,645 --> 01:07:55,737
...I heard on the news...

710
01:07:55,812 --> 01:08:00,443
...that an airline pilot spotted Santa's sled on its way in from New York.

711
01:08:06,322 --> 01:08:07,550
You serious, Clark?

712
01:08:10,595 --> 01:08:14,086
Load me up with a little more there. It's good.

713
01:08:24,944 --> 01:08:26,672
What's wrong with the dog?

714
01:08:30,349 --> 01:08:35,115
He's just yackin' on a bone. He's got it up. He's all right now.

715
01:08:36,922 --> 01:08:39,482
Maybe if you wouldn't feed him from the table...

716
01:08:41,027 --> 01:08:42,688
No.

717
01:08:43,529 --> 01:08:46,521
He's probably just nosing through the trash.

718
01:08:56,676 --> 01:08:59,043
If you're not doing anything constructive...

719
01:08:59,113 --> 01:09:01,741
...run into the living room, get my stogie.

720
01:09:03,216 --> 01:09:06,151
Is there anything else I can do for you, Uncle Louis?

721
01:09:06,586 --> 01:09:08,953
He's an old man. This may be his last Christmas.

722
01:09:10,157 --> 01:09:12,889
He keeps it up, it will be his last Christmas.

723
01:09:46,629 --> 01:09:47,926
That should be it.

724
01:10:04,347 --> 01:10:06,907
I told you, you had too many plugs in one outlet.

725
01:10:09,488 --> 01:10:10,419
What is it?

726
01:10:12,692 --> 01:10:15,627
Nothing. Let's go in and finish our dessert.

727
01:10:18,395 --> 01:10:21,456
If that thing had nine lives, she just spent them all.

728
01:10:26,472 --> 01:10:30,464
If you don't mind, I'd like to try to fumigate this here chair.

729
01:10:31,177 --> 01:10:32,974
It's a good quality item.

730
01:10:35,081 --> 01:10:39,143
If you don't mind me askin', how much it set you back?

731
01:10:40,186 --> 01:10:41,778
Do you smell something?

732
01:10:44,057 --> 01:10:45,489
Fried pussycat.

733
01:10:48,228 --> 01:10:51,857
It's not the chair, it's some kind of gas coming from the sewer.

734
01:11:41,850 --> 01:11:43,147
My tree!

735
01:11:45,354 --> 01:11:47,381
So, what's the matter with you?

736
01:11:48,392 --> 01:11:50,485
Look what you've done to my tree!

737
01:12:05,877 --> 01:12:07,845
It was an ugly tree anyway.

738
01:12:08,679 --> 01:12:10,739
At least it's out of its misery.

739
01:12:11,416 --> 01:12:13,440
- Dad's gonna flip out. - Nobody's gonna flip out.

740
01:12:13,518 --> 01:12:15,986
We're gonna have a wonderful Christmas.

741
01:12:19,559 --> 01:12:20,957
What the hell do you want?

742
01:12:21,026 --> 01:12:23,825
I have a delivery for Clark W. Griswold.

743
01:12:23,997 --> 01:12:26,227
I was supposed to deliver it yesterday...

744
01:12:26,366 --> 01:12:30,700
...but it fell between the seats and I didn't see it. I'm sorry.

745
01:12:37,878 --> 01:12:39,209
Merry Christmas.

746
01:12:40,447 --> 01:12:41,777
Merry Christmas.

747
01:12:45,719 --> 01:12:47,482
- I can't believe it. - What is it?

748
01:12:48,155 --> 01:12:50,989
A letter confirming your reservation at the nuthouse?

749
01:12:51,626 --> 01:12:52,820
It's from my company.

750
01:12:53,628 --> 01:12:54,423
Your bonus.

751
01:12:55,162 --> 01:12:56,060
My bonus.

752
01:13:01,835 --> 01:13:03,634
Open it, Clarkie. Open it.

753
01:13:04,307 --> 01:13:06,467
I hope it's a fortune.

754
01:13:07,142 --> 01:13:08,404
I bet you do.

755
01:13:13,281 --> 01:13:14,305
I was afraid...

756
01:13:14,582 --> 01:13:18,416
Are you going to bawl all over it, or are you gonna open it?

757
01:13:20,656 --> 01:13:24,524
I was gonna wait till tomorrow to tell you all this, but what the heck?

758
01:13:25,394 --> 01:13:28,762
With this bonus check, I'm putting in a swimming pool.

759
01:13:33,102 --> 01:13:35,333
That's it. That's the big one!

760
01:13:37,774 --> 01:13:38,832
Open it!

761
01:13:41,579 --> 01:13:45,014
I'm sorry if I've been a little short with everyone lately.

762
01:13:45,582 --> 01:13:47,379
I've been waiting for this bonus.

763
01:13:47,651 --> 01:13:49,780
To make sure the pool goes in when the ground thaws...

764
01:13:49,855 --> 01:13:51,845
...I had to lay out the money in advance.

